    array('title' => 'Max Headroom signal hijacking of WTTW', 'author' => '', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "The Max Headroom signal hijacking occurred on the night of November 22, 1987, when the television broadcasts of two stations in Chicago, Illinois were hijacked in an act of broadcast piracy by a video of an unknown person wearing a
Max Headroommask and costume, accompanied by distorted audio and a corrugated iron panel swiveling in the background to mimic Max Headroom's geometric background effect. This is a transcription of the second hijacking, which occurred at about 11:20 pm that night, when the signal of local PBS station WTTW was interrupted during an airing of the
Doctor Whoserial
Horror of Fang Rock. The hijacking lasted about 90 seconds before it shut off on its own.

Max Headroom
That does it, he's a freaking nerd. Yeah, I think I'm better than
Chuck Swirsky. Fricking liberal! Oh, Jesus!

Max Headroom
Your love is fading!

Max Headroom
Oh, I just made a giant masterpiece for all the
Greatest World Newspapernerds!

Max Headroom
My brother is wearing the other one, but it's dirty!

Max Headroom
Oh, no, they're coming to get me!

Max Headroom
Ahh! Oh, make it stop!

