    array('title' => 'Such a frolic before I think never was play\'d.', 'author' => '', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "Then his highness bespoke him a new suit and cloak,
Which he gave for the sake of this frolicksome joke;
Nay, and five hundred pound, with ten acres of ground,
Thou shalt never, said he, range the countries around,
Crying \"old brass to mend,\" for I'll be thy good friend,", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/25480'),
    array('title' => 'To the Newcastle that stands upon Tyne.', 'author' => '', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Sea songs', 'lyrics' => "Hast thou not heard, now, Henry Hunt,
As thou hast sailed by day and by night,
Of a Scottish rover on the seas;
Men call him sir Andrew Barton, knight?
Then ever he sighed, and said alas!
With a grieved mind, and well away!
But over-well I know that wight,", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/25480'),
    array('title' => 'You do not lightly ride out of your way.', 'author' => '', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "Why, what dost thou think of me, quoth our king merrily,
Passing thy judgment upon me so brief?
Good faith, said the miller, I mean not to flatter thee;
I guess thee to be but some gentleman thief;
Stand thee back, in the dark; light not adown,", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/25480'),
    array('title' => 'For to seek out the king in every town.', 'author' => '', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Love songs', 'lyrics' => "At last, at the miller's cot, soon they espy'd him out,
As he was mounting upon his fair steed;
To whom they came presently, falling down on their knee;
Which made the miller's heart wofully bleed;
Shaking and quaking, before him he stood,", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/25480'),
    array('title' => 'With bridles and saddles, and twenty things more.', 'author' => '', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "Tush, sir John, quo' his wife, why should you fret, or frown?
You shall ne'er be at no charges for me;
For I will turn and trim up my old russet gown,
With everything else as fine as may be;
And on our mill-horses swift we will ride,", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/25480'),
    array('title' => 'With pillows and pannels, as we shall provide.', 'author' => '', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "In this most stately sort, rode they unto the court,
Their jolly son Richard rode foremost of all;
Who set up, for good hap,[135] a cock's feather in his cap,
And so they jetted[136] down to the king's hall;
The merry old miller with hands on his side;", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/25480'),
    array('title' => 'London: WARD, LOCK, & TYLER, Warwick House, Paternoster Row.', 'author' => '', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Patriotic songs', 'lyrics' => "+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| TRANSCRIBER'S NOTE.                                                |
