Saying with freedom's ill-assum'd pretence,
'Tis noxious flattery, o'erwhelming sense.
Peace! scornful pride! nor with malignant aim
Belie the voice of consecrated fame,", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/8948'),
    array('title' => 'To every claim of their yet speaking dust.', 'author' => 'Hayley, William', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Sea songs', 'lyrics' => "Save me, good heaven! and all whom I regard,
(Or hasty muse, or irritable bard,)
