Marking how quick, in various hearts, arise
Those seeds of virtue, that thy verse supplies!
What joy, not speakable by mortal tongue,
What praises, to the harp of seraph sung,
May glad thee, now repaid for all thy woes,
While boundless vision to thy spirit shows", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/8948'),
    array('title' => 'Attain\'d the glorious aim, thy heart desired:', 'author' => 'Hayley, William', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Love songs', 'lyrics' => "Destin'd to spread, uncrampt by time or space,
