Epilogue", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Where I met but the human -- and sin.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "I walked in the world with the worldly;
I craved what the world never gave;
And I said:  \"In the world each Ideal,
That shines like a star on life's wave,
Is wrecked on the shores of the Real,
And sleeps like a dream in a grave.\"", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Veiled even that glimpse from my view.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Love songs', 'lyrics' => "And I toiled on, heart-tired, of the Human,
And I moaned 'mid the mazes of men,
Till I knelt, long ago, at an altar
And I heard a voice call me.  Since then
I walk down the Valley of Silence", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'That lies far beyond mortal ken.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Work songs', 'lyrics' => "Do you ask what I found in the Valley?
'Tis my Trysting Place with the Divine.
And I fell at the feet of the Holy,
And above me a voice said:  \"Be mine.\"
And there arose from the depths of my spirit
An echo -- \"My heart shall be Thine.\"", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Ascendeth to God night and day.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Hymns', 'lyrics' => "In the hush of the Valley of Silence
I dream all the songs that I sing;
And the music floats down the dim Valley,
Till each finds a word for a wing,
That to hearts, like the Dove of the Deluge,", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'In Life -- in Death -- kneel at his feet --', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Hymns', 'lyrics' => "Sweet in gladness, sweet in gloom,
Sweeter still beside the tomb.\"
Why should I wail?  Why ought I weep?
The grave -- it is not dark and deep;
Why should I sigh?  Why ought I moan?
The grave -- it is not still and lone;
Our God is sweet, our grave is sweet,
We lie there sleeping at His feet,
Where the wicked shall from troubling cease,
And weary hearts shall rest in peace!", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'In the wreaths which the brows of our past years have worn.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Love songs', 'lyrics' => "Yea! men will cling
With a love to the last,
And wildly fling
Their arms round their past!
As the vine that clings to the oak that falls;
As the ivy twines round the crumbled walls;
For the dust of the past some hearts higher prize", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Than the stars that flash out from the future\'s bright skies.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Love songs', 'lyrics' => "And why not so?
The old, Old Years,
They knew and they know
All our hopes and fears;
We walked by their side, and we told them each grief,
And they kissed off our tears while they whispered relief;
And the stories of hearts that may not be revealed", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Is the furrowed face of the Year that goes.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Love songs', 'lyrics' => "Yea! bright New Year,
O'er all the earth,
With song and cheer,
They will hail thy birth;
They will trust thy words in a single hour,
They will love thy face, they will laud thy power;
For the ~New~ has charms which the ~Old~ has not,
And the Stranger's face makes the Friend's forgot.", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Shall wave with a glory that never shall wane.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Sea songs', 'lyrics' => "Take it up! take it up! bear it back from afar!
That banner must blaze 'mid the lightnings of war;
Lay your hands on its folds, lift your gaze to the sky,
And swear that you'll bear it triumphant or die,
And shout to the clans scattered far o'er the earth
To join in the march to the land of their birth;
And wherever the Exiles, 'neath heaven's broad dome,
Have been fated to suffer, to sorrow and roam,
They'll bound on the sea, and away o'er the foam,
They'll sail to the music of \"Home, Sweet Home!\"", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'And blood and anguish of four deathless years.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "When Summer, like a rose in bloom,
Had blossomed from the bud of Spring,
Oh! who could deem the dews of doom
Upon the blushing lips could cling?
And who could believe its fragrant light
Would e'er be freighted with the breath of blight?", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'And bright with the deeds of the down-trodden just.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "Yes, give me the land where the battle's red blast
Has flashed to the future the fame of the past;
Yes, give me the land that hath legends and lays
That tell of the memories of long vanished days;
Yes, give me a land that hath story and song!
Enshrine the strife of the right with the wrong!
Yes, give me a land with a grave in each spot,
And names in the graves that shall not be forgot;
Yes, give me the land of the wreck and the tomb;
There is grandeur in graves -- there is glory in gloom;
For out of the gloom future brightness is born,
As after the night comes the sunrise of morn;
And the graves of the dead with the grass overgrown
May yet form the footstool of liberty's throne,
And each single wreck in the war path of might
Shall yet be a rock in the temple of right.", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'And sorrow leads me, Father, back to Thee.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "Amid the wrecks that mark the foeman's path
I kneel, and wailing o'er my glories gone,
I still each thought of hate, each throb of wrath,
And whisper, Father, let Thy will be done!
Pity me, Father of the desolate!
Alas! my burdens are so hard to bear;
Look down in mercy on my wretched fate,", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Whose sun never passeth away.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "And I knew the voice; not a sweeter
On earth or in Heaven can be;
And never did shadow pass fleeter
Than it and its strange melody;
And I know I must hasten to meet her,
\"Yea, ~Sister!~ thou callest to me!\"", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Had smiled on me sweetly before.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Folk songs', 'lyrics' => "And I saw the hand with the garland,
Ethel's hand -- holy and fair;
Who went long ago to the far-land
To weave me the wreath I shall wear;
And to-night I look up to the star-land,
And pray that I soon may be there.", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'The Angels of Mary were there.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Hymns', 'lyrics' => "Ah, faith! simple faith of the children!
You still shame the faith of the old!
Ah, love! simple love of the little,
You still warm the love of the cold!
And the beautiful God who is wandering
Far out in the world's dreary wold,
Finds a home in the hearts of the children", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'And a rest with the lambs of the fold.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Hymns', 'lyrics' => "Swept a voice:  was it wafted from Heaven?
Heard you ever the sea when it sings
Where it sleeps on the shore in the night time?
Heard you ever the hymns the breeze brings
From the hearts of a thousand bright summers?
Heard you ever the bird, when she springs
To the clouds, till she seems to be only
A song of a shadow on wings?", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'With its perfume of worship was filled.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Hymns', 'lyrics' => "Then back to the Queen-Virgin's altar
The white veils swept on, two by two;
And the holiest halo of heaven
Flashed out from the ribbons of blue;
And they laid down the wreaths of the roses
Whose hearts were as pure as their hue;
Ah! they to the Christ are the truest,
Whose loves to the Mother are true!", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'With thee all days to dwell.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Love songs', 'lyrics' => "From his hand to his lips that tremble,
From his lips to his heart a-thrill,
Goes the little Host on its love-path,
Still doing the Father's will;
And over the rim of the chalice
The blood flows forth to fill", 'source_url' => 'https://gutendex.com/books/937'),
    array('title' => 'Still beats in the holy place.', 'author' => 'Ryan, Abram Joseph', 'year' => '', 'category' => 'Hymns', 'lyrics' => "The priest comes down to the railing
Where brows are bowed in prayer;
In the tender clasp of his fingers
